layerGroup.title: Multi-resolution categorised acoustic seabed hardness of the Australian margin (CSIRO/NESP)
layerGroup.abstractTxt:
A collation of seabed backscatter data from multibeam bathymetry surveys of the Australian margin held by CSIRO in or around 2010. The layer group includes data gridded at both low (~300m) and high (~30m) resolutions, with higher-resolution data prioritised where overlaps occur.
The acoustic reflectance intensity is broadly classified into three categories, indicating likely soft, moderate/mixed, and hard seabed compositions.
